The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Jindal Hotels Ltd will make a 1:2 rights issue one equity share for every two held subject to approval of shareholders. The shares will be issued at a premium of Rs 10-20 per share. The exact price of the shares will be announced while filing the letter of offer to Sebi.

 Kohlberg Kravis Roberts, Silver Lake Partners and AlpInvest Partners have jointly signed an agreement with Philips Electronics to pick up an 80.1 per cent stake in the Dutch companys semiconductor business.

 Punj Lloyd Ltd has received a contract from Yemens Yemgas a joint venture among Technip France, JCG Corporation and Kellogg-Brown amp; Root Inc for construction and off-site painting works. The project is slated to be completed in 28 months. 

 Asian CERC Information Technology Ltds net profit for the year ended March 2006 was Rs 1.72 crore against Rs 56 lakh a year ago. Income from operations rose to Rs 8.88 crore from Rs 4.01 crore a year ago. Revenues from content and data feed was Rs 2.12 crore.

 ASUSTek Computer Inc has formed a joint venture with Gigabyte Technology to produce Gigabyte branded motherboards and graphic cards. Gigabyte will control 51 per cent of the merged entity and ASUSTek will control the remainder.

 LifeScan, a division of Johnson and Johnson Medical (J amp;J), has launched OneTouch helpline Service. The service will provide information related to diabetes management and details on the OneTouch range of blood glucose monitoring devices. 

 Hewitt Associates will launch Hewitt Best Employers in India 2007 study in September. This is part of the Hewitt Best Employers in Asia 2007 study, which spans the key markets of China, Hong Kong, Japan, Korea and Singapore. 

 The National Mineral Development Corporation (NMDC) has paid Rs 356.57 crore as dividend to the centre. NMDCs revenue was Rs 3,710.92 crore and gross profit was Rs 2,883.82 crore for 2006. 

 Alembic Ltds net profit rose 68.51 per cent to Rs 18.25 crore for the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 10.83 crore a year ago. Total income was Rs 149.03 crore compared with Rs 137.57 crore.

 NTPC Vindhyachal has been commissioned to set up its first stage III 500-mw unit at Vindhyanagar, Madhya Pradesh. The company is already constructing its second stage III 500-mw unit.

